			<p class="intable" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:#B22222;"><strong>Trumping User Fees</strong></span></p>

			<center style="text-align: left;">The Trump Administration is proposing to double User Fee receipts from USD 1.2 to 2.4 Billion, on average doubling drug and device user fees. So if you were thinking of a complex US Submission, getting it in quickly could save you thousands!</center>
			</td>
			<td>
			<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Standards Nightmare</strong></p>

			<p class="intable">Not only are we still smarting under DG SANCO&#39;s rewrite of ISO 14971 to a slavish letter-of-the-law interpretation of the directive, but now&nbsp;ISO TC 210 has accepted DIS 3 so ISO 13485 will not follow the Annex SL format, which is used for&nbsp;all other management system standards including ISO 9001:2015 - when will the regulators stop trying to fiddle standards to suit their needs rather than accept the sound quality philosophy underlying the standards process? This will&nbsp;force many device companies to drop ISO 9001. How sad to see quality principles being compromised by the regulators who claim to value them!&nbsp;</p>

			<p><img alt="Come and talk to use about your quality and risk issues" height="157" src="images/C0927CompaMed0Asmall.JPG" title="After being asleep for two years, Amanda will be fresh and bright for our return to ComPaMED" width="272" /></p>

